snippet.textDisplay: Hey brother, just found your site and subscribed. I used to do some writing for Corvette Enthusiast magazine before it went under. Are you aware of Jason Francis? He has an old Coca Cola warehouse in Streator, IL (just North of Bloomington). His business is www.vette2vette.com. He buys 1984 and up Corvette wrecks and parts them out. I believe he has been in business about 20 years and gives wonderful service to his customers. Gordon Killebrew, a NCM Hall of Fame inductee, has long been known as one of the C4 gurus. Gordon never had a son and has semi-adopted Jason. Gordon has passed along many of his testing tools and knowledge to Jason. He knows C4s and has any parts and advice you might need. I am looking forward to your project!
